[[cdo:9 nguŏk 27 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:9 goe̍h 27 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:九月廿七]] {{Lunisolar September}} '''September 27''' is the 27th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft}} , the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} and its day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Wadō|ja|文和|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1352|ja|1352|12=draft}} {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|12=draft}} ） – The Northern Court ({{ill|Kitachō|ja|北朝|12=draft}} ) changed its era name from {{ill|Kangō|ja|Kan'ō|12=draft}} to {{ill|Bunwa|ja|文和|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Man'en|ja|万延|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1860|ja|1860|12=draft}} {{ill|November 9|ja|11月9日|12=draft}} ） – A 77-member mission to America ({{ill|Emissary to America|ja|遣米使節団|12=draft}} ) returned home after signing the [[Treaty of Amity and Commerce (United States–Japan)|Japan–US Treaty of Amity and Commerce]].
== Births == * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft}} 12nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1829|ja|1829|12=draft}} {{ill|October 24|ja|10月24日|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Takeichi Mizusan|ja|武市瑞山|12=draft}} (Hanpeita), a pro-sonnō activist and swordsman († {{ill|1865|ja|1865|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Yōchō|ja|弘化|12=draft}} 5th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} {{ill|1848|ja|1848|12=draft}} {{ill|October 23|ja|10月23日|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Nakagawa Gorōji|ja|中川五郎治|12=draft}} , considered the founder of variolation († {{ill|1768|ja|1768|12=draft}} ).
