{{Not to be confused with|September 27}}<!--hatnote--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:17, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月廿七|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 27일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 27''' is the 27th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} , the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} and its day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}} .
== Events == * [[:en:Bunna|Wadō]] 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1352|ja|1352|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1352|qq=}} [[:en:November 4|November 4]] ） – The Northern Court ({{ill|Kitachō|ja|北朝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitachō|qq=}} ) changed its era name from {{ill|Kangō|ja|Kan'ō|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kangō|qq=}} to [[:en:Bunna|Bunwa]] . * [[:en:Man'en|Man'en]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1860|ja|1860|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1860|qq=}} [[:en:November 9|November 9]] ） – A 77-member mission to America ({{ill|Emissary to America|ja|遣米使節団|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emissary to America|qq=}} ) returned home after signing the [[Treaty of Amity and Commerce (United States–Japan)|Japan–US Treaty of Amity and Commerce]].
== Births == * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 12nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1829|ja|1829|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1829|qq=}} [[:en:October 24|October 24]] ） – [[:en:Takechi Hanpeita|Takeichi Mizusan]] (Hanpeita), a pro-sonnō activist and swordsman († {{ill|1865|ja|1865|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1865|qq=}} ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kōka|Yōchō]] 5th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1848|ja|1848|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1848|qq=}} [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ） – {{ill|Nakagawa Gorōji|ja|中川五郎治|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakagawa Gorōji|qq=}} , considered the founder of variolation († {{ill|1768|ja|1768|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1768|qq=}} ).
